 ```
 
+### Retargeting from HumanML / MDM to Robot
+
+For HumanML3D or MDM-style results such as `results.npy`, GMR provides a lightweight adapter that:
+
+- reads a 22-joint motion sequence from `results.npy` or a compatible `.npz`
+- estimates human height from the sequence
+- interpolates the motion from `20 fps` to `30 fps`
+- converts the joint trajectory into the per-frame human pose dictionary expected by GMR
+
+Retarget a single sequence:
+
+```bash
+python scripts/humanml_to_robot.py \
+  --motion_file <path_to_results.npy> \
+  --robot unitree_g1 \
+  --sample_idx 0 \
+  --repetition_idx 0 \
+  --save_path <path_to_save_robot_data.pkl> \
+  --rate_limit
+```
+
+Example:
+
+```bash
+python scripts/humanml_to_robot.py \
+  --motion_file /home/hjj/AnyMotion/src/motion-diffusion-model/save/humanml_trans_dec_512_bert/samples_humanml_trans_dec_512_bert_000600000_seed10_a_man_is_boxing_and_fighting/results.npy \
+  --robot unitree_g1 \
+  --sample_idx 0 \
+  --repetition_idx 0 \
+  --save_path retargeting_data/humanml_boxing_g1.pkl \
+  --rate_limit
+```
+render:
+```
+python scripts/vis_robot_motion.py --robot unitree_g1 --robot_motion_path retargeting_data/humanml_boxing_g1.pkl
+```
+
+
+Notes:
+
+- `--sample_idx` selects one generated sample.
+- `--repetition_idx` selects one repetition for that sample.
+- `--sequence_idx` can be used instead of `--sample_idx/--repetition_idx` to address the flattened sequence directly.
+- `--source_fps` defaults to the file metadata when present, otherwise `20`.
+- `--target_fps` defaults to `30`.
+- `--human_height` can override the automatic height estimate if needed.
+- `--no_visualize` runs the conversion and optional export without opening MuJoCo.
 
 
